Description: Fender 60th anniversary, FENDER special run (FSR) America Select HSS Stratocaster in beautiful crimson transparent red. 2006.The frets have been professionally buffed, rosewood fingerboard cleaned and oiled and brand new 9 gauge strings.This American Select Stratocaster is in high quality, very good condition. These are basically an American Deluxe Strat with a mahogony body and are becoming hard to find. The mahogany sounds amazing with the humbucker in the bridge!Comes with aftermarket case. No trem arm.Specs from fender:The serial number DZ610**** is in our database as a Fender FSR American Select Stratocaster HSS (Mahogany), in Crimson Transparent, made in November of 2006. Originally introduced as an Anniversary model with SCN pickups. It was also released by GC under the name, “American Special Series”. When we introduced the American Special Series instruments,...the name of these were changed from American Special to American Select. When the price point of the American Deluxe guitars went up, GC wanted to keep this guitar in their lineup at the same price point. This was achieved by replacing the pickguard assembly with an American Series loaded with Tex-Mex pickups.
